When the eggs hatch the chicks are put under the{electric hen.}Two weeks later they are put out into a high wire pen with a{netting roof.} When they have their adult feathers at about 4 weeks they are in a pen {without a top.}
Foxes,weasels,stoats and hawks are {enemies}of the young chick. The Gamekeeper rears 3.000 chicks ready for the{October Shoot.}He also rears a few ducks and partridges. By October the young birds must be well grown or they will not survive in the wild.
At the{Shoot}he organizes the{ {beaters}and takes his 2{spaniels}to{ {flush out}and{drive}the birds while the {labrador retrieves}the shot birds. Only half of the reared birds are shot during the season.
